title: Bitcoin price soars above $11000 as central bankers seek to calm fears
paragraph: Bitcoin topped $11,000 on Wednesday, less than 24 hours after hitting $10,000 for the first time, as central bankers on both sides of the Atlantic sought to ease fears that a potential bubble in the cryptocurrency was a threat to the global economy ...

title: Bank of England Chief: Bitcoin Isn't a Threat to Financial Stability
paragraph: Bank of England governor Mark Carney has said that bitcoin's meteoric price gains do not pose a threat to global financial stability.
